====================================================================
PROJECT DATASET SOURCE & DOWNLOAD INSTRUCTIONS
====================================================================

Project Name: Fake News Detection System
Dataset Name: ISOT Fake News Dataset
Source Platform: Kaggle

Official Download Link:
👉 https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/csmalarkodi/isot-fake-news-dataset

--------------------------------------------------------------------
STEP-BY-STEP DOWNLOAD & SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
--------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Open your web browser and navigate to the link above.
2. Log in to your Kaggle account (or sign up for a free account if 
   you do not have one).
3. Click the blue "Download" button located on the top-right corner 
   of the dataset header to fetch the archive.
4. Locate the downloaded file on your local machine (typically saved 
   as a compressed 'archive.zip' file).
5. Extract the contents of the ZIP folder. You will find two core files:
   - Fake.csv
   - True.csv
6. Move or copy both 'Fake.csv' and 'True.csv' directly into your 
   main 'Fake_News_Detection' root project folder next to your 
   development notebook ('main.ipynb').

--------------------------------------------------------------------
DATASET ARCHITECTURE SPECIFICATIONS:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
- Total Sample Columns: title, text, subject, date
- Targets Handled:
  * Fake.csv -> Mapped internally to Target Label: 1
  * True.csv -> Mapped internally to Target Label: 0
